<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-08T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68/296: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Smyrna</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Horton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Smyrna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-08T22:00:00+03:00"><hi rend="italic">September 8,
                                        1922—10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September 9—12:22
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Turkish forces expected to arrive tomorrow night or morning after. Please
                            telegraph urgently what will be my relations if any with the Kemalist
                            military or civil authorities.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Horton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>